Make sure you wash your hands well
We all know that you have to wash them (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that to actually get rid of germs, you need to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30–40 seconds to wash away dangerous bacteria and viruses from your hands
And most of us wash them shorter!
Just warm water and ordinary soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even reject it).
When washing, we rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hands, but also: fingertips (joined or alone) – rub them with circular movements on the inside of the other hand, spaces between the fingers (swipe hands, rubbing the fingers together), thumbs – each thumb we cover with the other hand and in such an embrace we turn it for a while to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when you can't wash your hands) you should wipe your hands with a wet cloth, and then use antibacterial gel (in pharmacies, from 5 PLN).
When using the public toilet, do not touch the handles or doors with washed hands (recommendation of the Main Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open them with a paper towel.
Iranian President says he rejected the proposal for talks with the US, Donald Trump denies
Tehran did not enter into talks with the American side during the UN General Assembly in New York, despite the offer of the Americans to lift the sanctions – said Iranian President Hasan Rowhani on Friday.
President Donald Trump said that the Iranian side had asked for the ban to be lifted, but he did not agree.
Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said that the United States had proposed to lift all sanctions against Tehran in exchange for negotiating a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear program and its ballistic missile program.
Rowhani: Iran will not enter talks under maximum pressure
The Iranian President said he did not agree to the talks because of the "toxic atmosphere".
He was also a member of the United States delegation to the United Nations, where he met with the representatives of France, Germany and the United Kingdom.
He said that Iran would not enter into talks under "maximum pressure".
"Even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in the 5+1 format, no one can predict what the final outcome will be," Rowhani said.
The day before, the Iranian leader said that he was not excluding talks with the US, and he accused the European parties of promoting US sanctions on Iran.
He added that sanctions imposed on Iran after the US withdrawal from the nuclear deal "are a precondition that does not allow" for dialogue.
If we can remove this precondition and if America lifts the sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America," he declared.
He added that he would not rule out meeting with US President Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a meeting during the UN General Assembly this week.
Trump: “Iran asked, I said no”
Donald Trump has said on Twitter that he has rejected the Iranian side's request.
"Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions on them so that we could meet.
Of course I said 'no!' tweeted the US President.
Nuclear tension in the background
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease tensions between Washington and Tehran in order to somehow salvage the 2015 agreement with Iran to which they were signatories.
The Iranian government has announced that it will abandon its nuclear weapons program and place the nuclear sector under the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the US withdrew from the agreement in May 2015, the remaining signatories have repeatedly confirmed their willingness to keep the agreement in force.
So far, none of this has worked.
Washington is using a maximum pressure tactics on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has announced that if it does not receive a permit to export raw materials, it will limit its commitments under the agreement every 60 days.
