Feel the game with Razer Nari Ultimate for Xbox One
Razer announced the Razer Nari Ultimate for Xbox One, the world's first haptic-powered headset for Xbox One.
HyperSense provides immersion in games and provides better control over the environment.
The HyperSense Razer uses haptic solutions developed by Lofelt, a German company specializing in the creation of advanced haptic technologies for realistic touch-based experiences.
HyperSense uses special haptic controllers and intelligent digital signal processing to generate high-resolution, real-time touch feedback, giving you the ability to immerse yourself in every game on Xbox One.
The technology recognizes sound signals and converts them into dynamic vibrations, so players can feel the game without the need to install additional software.
Using the sense of touch, the sound signals can accurately mimic the actions in the game.
HyperSense Razer plays back events – from silent steps to powerful explosions, accurately reflecting all the activities in the player's environment.
“Nari Ultimate for Xbox One is designed to give all players an extra dimension to the game.
With HyperSense, we allow them to completely immerse themselves in their favorite titles,” said Alvin Cheung, Senior Vice President of Peripherals at Razer.
The rotary earbuds feature foam-filled pillows with shape memory and a layer of cooling gel to limit the heat generated during long use.
For even easier handling of the headphones, a quick mute button is placed on the sliding microphone, and the headphone case has a HyperSense intensity regulator and a balance slider between game and chat.
The self-adaptive headband provides a seamless and accurate fit.
In addition, Razer Nari Ultimate for Xbox One features Xbox Wireless, which allows you to connect directly to your console without the need for a wireless TV or radio, allowing for easy and fast setup.
The headphones also support Windows Sonic, which provides a more realistic sound.
Razer Nari Ultimate, originally designed for PCs, debuted on the market in September 2018.
With Nari Ultimate for Xbox One, Razer can now offer this award-winning technology to Xbox One fans.
The set was priced at 219,99 euros.
